  "response": "Here are some basics of audio devices and sound:\n\n1. Sound Basics:\n- Sound is a vibration that travels through a medium (air, water, solid)\n- Measured in waves with frequency and amplitude\n- Travels at approximately 343 meters/second in air\n\n2. Key Sound Characteristics:\n- Frequency (pitch): Number of sound waves per second\n- Amplitude (volume): Height of sound waves\n- Wavelength\n- Decibel (dB): Measure of sound intensity\n\n3. Audio Device Types:\n- Speakers\n- Headphones\n- Microphones\n- Amplifiers\n- Sound cards\n- Audio interfaces\n\n4. Audio Signal Types:\n- Analog signals\n- Digital signals\n- Balanced vs. unbalanced signals\n\n5. Speaker Specifications:\n- Frequency response\n- Impedance\n- Sensitivity\n- Power handling\n- Driver size\n\n6. Microphone Types:\n- Dynamic\n- Condenser\n- Ribbon\n- Omnidirectional\n- Cardioid\n- Bidirectional\n\n7. Audio Connections:\n- 3.5mm jack\n- XLR\n- RCA\n- USB\n- Optical\n- HDMI\n\n8. Audio Processing:\n- Equalization (EQ)\n- Compression\n- Reverb\n- Filtering",
